mber}"}, "commits": {"href": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails-girls-summer-of-code/rgsoc-teams/pulls/159/commits"}, "statuses": {"href": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails-girls-summer-of-code/rgsoc-teams/statuses/e392f7b7d66b587c46b5911f95b7aef87e64ec94"}}, "author_association": "MEMBER", "body_html": "<p>This addresses the first item on <a href=\"https://github.com/rails-girls-summer-of-code/rgsoc-teams/issues/144\" class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load issue title\" data-id=\"59447926\" data-permission-text=\"Issue title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/rails-girls-summer-of-code/rgsoc-teams/issues/144\">#144</a> (Send an email when added to a team).</p>\n<p>A few notes on what I have done:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>I have monkey patched Mail::Message to respond to <code>:deliver_later</code> in <code>config/initializers/monkey_patch_mail.rb</code>. I've done this to make upgrading to Rails 4.2 easier when we have ActiveJob available. It essentially puts the mailer in a background job. This should be removed when upgrading to 4.2 .</li>\n<li>I've added the <a href=\"https://github.com/ddollar/foreman\">foreman gem</a>. It is nicer and easier to have your environment variables in a <code>.env</code> file. I've also added <code>.env</code> to the .gitignore file. I can update the readme to reflect this in the Mailtrap section.</li>\n<li>I had a bit of trouble with other tests failing because they were trying to deliver the email. I've set <code>action_mailer.raise_delivery_errors</code> to <code>false</code>. Let me know if this is unacceptable, and I'll find another way.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href=\"https://camo.githubusercontent.com/344ed03102f0d870fbcffb04e84918764cfe525f/687474703a2f2f692e696d6775722e636f6d2f346e51616346332e676966\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://camo.githubusercontent.com/344ed03102f0d870fbcffb04e84918764cfe525f/687474703a2f2f692e696d6775722e636f6d2f346e51616346332e676966\" alt=\"Wiggle\" data-canonical-src=